# How to use Event Manager in Plesk


The Event Manager is used to run scripts whenever certain events occur in Plesk.

In order to add event handler that triggers the event processing, first login to your Plesk administrative panel as admin and do the following steps:

1) Click on **Tools & Utilities** from the **Home** page and then click on **Event Manager**.


2) Then click on **Add new Event Handler** and an **Event handler property** section will be displayed.

3) Then choose the event that will trigger the command, set the priority,  select the system user with which the command will be executed and specify a command to be executed when the selected event occurs and then click **OK**.
